5176	\begin{lemma}
5177	[Cocycle property of the Serre-twist transitions]
5178	  \label{lem:serre_twist_cocycle}
5179	  \leanok
5180	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.ProjTwist.twistTransition_cocycle}
5181	  \uses{lem:serre_twist_transition_unit}
5182	  On \(\operatorname{Proj} \mathbb{Z}[X_i : i \in n]\), for each \(m \ge 0\)
5183	  the multiplication maps by \((X_i/X_j)^m\) on the trivial line bundles over
5184	  the basic opens \(D_+(X_i)\), transported to the pairwise scheme-theoretic
5185	  overlaps of the cover, satisfy the descent cocycle condition on triple
5186	  overlaps: over \(D_+(X_i) \cap D_+(X_j) \cap D_+(X_k)\),
5187	  \[
5188	    \left(\frac{X_j}{X_k}\right)^{m}
5189	    \left(\frac{X_i}{X_j}\right)^{m}
5190	    \;=\; \left(\frac{X_i}{X_k}\right)^{m},
5191	  \]
5192	  compatibly with the identifications of the restricted trivial bundles.
5193	\end{lemma}
5194	
5195	\begin{proof}
5196	  \uses{lem:serre_twist_transition_unit}
5197	  In the degree-zero part of the localization
5198	  \(\mathbb{Z}[X_i]_{X_i X_j X_k}\), the three fractions satisfy
5199	  \((X_i/X_j)(X_j/X_k) = X_i/X_k\) since
5200	  \(X_i^2 X_j^2 X_k^2 = (X_i X_j)(X_j X_k)(X_i X_k)\); raising to the
5201	  \(m\)-th power preserves the identity.  The multiplication maps by these
5202	  units on the trivial line bundles commute with restriction to smaller
5203	  opens, because multiplication by a section commutes with the restriction
5204	  maps of the structure sheaf; and the trivialization comparisons between
5205	  the restricted bundles compose transitively.  Hence the transported
5206	  transition isomorphisms compose as claimed.
5207	\end{proof}
